stepTitle: The terminal velocity of a person falling in air depends upon the weight and the area of the person facing the fluid. Find the terminal velocity (in meters per second) of an $$80.0kg$$ skydiver falling in a headfirst position with a cross-section area facing the fluid of $$0.14m^2$$. Assume the density of air is $$1.21$$ $$\frac{kg}{m^3}$$
